li.p:
For each of the following matrices, explain why it is not in reduced row
echelon form.

                        {{#non_rrefs}}
                            {{label}} = {{matrix}} \hspace{2em}
                        {{/non_rrefs}}
                        \hspace{2em}

answer.ul:
            {{#non_rrefs}}




{{label}}={{matrix}} is not in reduced row echelon form because
                        {{#elementary}}
not every entry above and below each pivot is zero.
                        {{/elementary}}
                        {{#permutation}}
the pivots are not descending to the right.
                        {{/permutation}}
                        {{#diagonal}}
the pivots are not all 1.
                        {{/diagonal}}


            {{/non_rrefs}}
